headline: Head of Engineering at Fieldguide
about: I am a software engineer and manager with experience delivering applications to millions of users. I build teams with strong bonds of trust, responsibility, and continuous refinement.

experience.description: As Head of Engineering at Fieldguide, I lead our team in building innovative AI-powered solutions that transform auditing and advisory workflows. I focus on scaling our products, driving technical excellence, and fostering a collaborative, high-performing culture to help our customers succeed.

I lead three product engineering teams responsible for building the next generation of AI- and ML-driven features in Asana. Some of our groundbreaking launches include AI Chat (powered by retrieval-augmented generation), Smart Status, Smart Summaries, Smart Answers, and more.

I am responsible for the delivery of my teams' business outcomes, as well as setting the overall technical strategy, organizational design, and partnering closely on matters of product strategy, compliance, and sales enablement.

I led an engineering org with over 60 engineers, including six engineering managers. Together with my partners in Product, Design, Data Science, and UXR, we build features and improvements to Asana to make it as easy as possible for users to discover Asana.

My teams have built massive new features like the Project Grid, Home, shareable views, and the Workflow Builder. We've also launched countless optimizations and improvements to the new user journey with measurable impact on business outcomes.

I was also the primary engineering manager responsible for Asana’s early career hiring. My work has brought over 100 new engineers into the company and significantly improved the diversity of the engineering team.

I am proud to have learned the craft of people management at Asana. In my time as a front-line manager, I had the opportunity to work with several product engineering teams focusing on new user adoption, monetization, administrative features, and core product functionality.
I led the engineering team responsible for internationalizing the product, making it available in multiple languages and currencies for the first time.

• grew show from 80,000 downloads per month to 210,000 per month

headline: Working with the world’s best founders from seed to IPO & beyond
about:
Don is passionate about working with entrepreneurs who build durable, generational businesses and is an early backer of ten $1B+ "unicorns." His most well-known investment was in Deel where he wrote the largest seed check and enlisted numerous executives for key roles. He brokered hundreds of strategic partnership introductions which now account for very significant revenue.

Previously, he co-founded CityDeal, a b2b marketing technology business, which was exited to Groupon in the early days. Then, he built and ran Groupon's international offices with 500+ employees spanning Europe and Asia. He subsequently led BD at Airbnb globally and launched multiple offices both organically and through M&A. He constructed and ran the original high end listing and long term stays initiatives, which are multi-billion dollar revenue generating product categories today - LTS now accounts for 20%+ of Airbnb's revenue. Simultaneously, Don advised a variety of high growth startups such as Handy, which was an early Airbnb partner and made a marked impact on global listing quality. He has a track record of succeeding in highly competitive markets and has built or backed numerous tech industry leaders

While an investment banker at Credit Suisse tech M&A group in San Francisco, Don worked on George Boutros' team on multiple blockbuster multi-billion dollar deals, including Submarino/Lojas Americanas (B2W), Google/Youtube, Google/DoubleClick, and many more

During his junior and senior years in high school, Don ran a six figure online marketplace, which sold virtual and real world goods to Ultima Online and Everquest gamers. He went to the University of Minnesota for the majority of his high school course load and while in college at the University of Chicago, he attended courses with Nobel Laureate professors Robert Fogel and Gary Becker. His honors thesis surrounded the economic, anthropological and cultural impacts of the reunification of Germany

experience.description: software-defined, input-to-outcome automation

The Airbnb diaspora produced tremendous startups, unicorns, funds & consultancies, and I’ve been lucky to have a front row seat along the way

I joined early days (2011) alongside a contract advisory group and wore hats including growth, ops and BD. We hired GMs globally, implemented new mkt playbooks, P&Ls - and developed and instituted new product lines such as Long Term Stays, High End, host and guest tools and services. New products that emerged have made a meaningful impact today - incidentally, Long Term Stays accounts for 10%+ (and growing!) of Airbnb's revenue. And the model led to a new class of startups - Boatsetter (boating), Onefinestay (Luxury), Swimply (pools), and more

Geo expansion was complex, but also exhilarating - Airbnb Australia’s opening drew thousands from around Oceania and SEA and let to significant bookings and revenue. Passion was felt when we assembled at Sydney’s Cockatoo Island for our launch. Airbnb’s founders, investors and employees huddled together with thousands to celebrate

During this period, reducing friction for hosts and guests was crucial; we tracked 13 KPIs, including check-in, checkout, location & cleanliness of a property. This led us to research services and startups catering to alternative accommodations —  laundry, food delivery, transportation. And it turns out on-demand cleaning was accelerating rapidly alongside Airbnb’s growth. Handybook, which shared co-investors with Airbnb, was the top player in the space, alongside the likes of Homejoy and multiple others. In fact, Airbnb built a customer service team dedicated to cleaning — and I took note.  Off the back of a number of tests, I decided to move over to Handy to help reduce the friction at Airbnb and orchestrated new product launches and staffing and is still used by many Airbnb hosts today

Over the past decade, I’ve supported a variety of Airbnb alumni, including the spectacular AirAngels - a seed fund led by Airbnb alumni, where I’m an active advisor today

about:
I believe the best leaders excel at uniting teams by driving alignment and collaboration around a cohesive vision and strategy. Bringing people together and establishing strong trust, integrity and accountability based relationships to achieve shared goals and deliver high-impact results is my secret sauce.
 
With over 20 years of experience, I have built and scaled organizations, programs and high-performing teams that consistently drive record growth in both startup and large enterprise environments.  

My passion is formulating strategies and building/leading winning teams that drive results.  I'm fortunate to have had the opportunity to do so in a variety of executive leadership roles, including co-founding Partner of an international risk advisory firm, General Manager of an industry leading GRC SaaS business, and most recently Global Head of Partnerships for the enterprise reporting global SaaS leader.  

As Head of Global Partnerships, I love bringing organizations together to discover and execute on win-win value propositions that solve impactful customer problems, create differentiation, produce innovation and drive significant accretive revenue.  I have proven that with the right strategy, team, organizational support & alignment, focus and discipline, alliances can be a true force multiplier in accelerating revenue growth.

I thrive in high-pressure environments, where I embrace ambiguity and enjoy tackling challenging problems. Known for my exceptional communication skills, strong business acumen, and ability to build relationships at all levels, I bring poise, positivity, and a constant drive to challenge the status quo, as I build, lead, and mentor highly engaged teams that deliver results!

experience.position: Vice President, Head of Partnerships & Alliances
SVP, Head of Global Partnerships & Alliances
experience.description:
Workiva (NYSE: WK) is the leading global cloud provider (SaaS) of assured integrated reporting solutions for Financial Reporting, Governance, Risk & Compliance (GRC), and Sustainability (ESG); used by thousands of companies across 120 countries, including more than 80% of the Fortune 500 and government agencies. 

As Head of Global Partnerships & Alliances, I have strategic leadership responsibility for Workiva's 200+ global partner and alliance channel network.  Workiva's Partner ecosystem includes system integrators (global and regional), advisory/consulting, enterprise technology, cloud hyperscalers, distributors, design agencies, law firms, resell and managed services (MSP) firms of all sizes, including the world's leading global enterprises. 

Reporting to the CEO (member of executive leadership team), in addition to leading the global alliances teams, lead the company's outsourcing/MSP sales channel as well as the global Partner Sales, Partner Marketing, Partner Operations and Partner Solutions teams.

I developed a global Go-to-Market strategy, expanded the alliances team, refined our partner ecosystem and implemented programs and processes to support global scale. This included overhauling the channel strategy and strengthening relationships with major system integrators, cloud and enterprise technology partners in addition to building new ecosystem channels.

By implementing a strategic partnership management framework focused on partner fit, market segmentation, accountability and growth, I significantly grew channel ACV (400%), increased Partner attach rate from 30% to >70% of bookings, expanded and diversified our channel pipeline, and tripled the number of high-revenue contributing partners over 3 years.

Led Workiva's global GRC business (General Manager), with strategic leadership and P&L accountability for a portfolio of solutions, including Controls Management, Internal Audit Management, Enterprise Risk Management (ERM), IT Risk & Compliance and Policies & Procedures.

Responsible for cross functional leadership and strategic alignment of the dedicated global sales, product marketing, product management, R&D, client services, solution engineering, customer success and partnership teams supporting the overall success of the business. With limited direct reports, I drove significant change through influence and cross-functional collaboration.

I improved overall business performance and revenue contribution by repositioning our offerings, working closely with sales and marketing to refine and enhance our brand, and improve competitiveness. Developed a 3-year business and product strategy and corresponding business case that resulted in increased investments towards product capabilities and performance.  Was a key stakeholder supporting due diligence and other M&A related activity.  

In collaboration with the Customer Success team, I implemented an innovative customer engagement and renewal model to improve client retention amid growing competition; as our product transformed from a secondary offering to a critical component of an enterprise platform.

Responsible for leading all consulting, service delivery, customer on-boarding and Partner enablement for Workiva's GRC business unit.

My GRC expertise and background in professional services made me the ideal candidate for this newly-created position leading Workiva’s team of 30 Solution Architects and Onboarding Project Managers. Together, we tackled some of the most complex challenges in GRC—ranging from internal audits to SOX compliance and risk management.

I quickly identified opportunities for improvement and spearheaded the redesign of the customer onboarding process. This initiative not only enhanced the quality of our service delivery but also significantly accelerated the time-to-value for our clients, driving greater customer satisfaction and retention.

Formed from the merger of Sunera, APTEC, and ANRC, Focal Point provides business and technology risk consulting services in cyber security, data privacy, data analytics, identity risk (IAM), internal audit & compliance.

As a Founding Partner, I helped transform Sunera (later Focal Point) from an eight-person team into an international consulting disruptor with over 200 employees and ~$50M in revenue. I launched and scaled operations in Canada and the U.S. West Coast, driving market growth through strategic GTM execution, delivery excellence and P&L management. By hiring and empowering top talent, I built high-performing teams and maintained a strong corporate culture with low attrition rates. In addition to the geographic leadership responsibilities, I built and led the firm's national data analytics practice, establishing GTM partnerships with leading analytics technology platforms.  Post-private equity acquisition, I co-led the integration of 15 national practices, driving significant revenue growth.

WestJet is the 2nd largest Canadian Air Carrier, with $4.5B in revenue and fleet size of 170, providing service to over 107 destinations.  The airline averaged 25% YOY growth during my tenure. 

I joined this newly-public airline to establish its internal audit function from the ground up. Reporting to the CFO and the Board Audit Committee, I quickly built trust and implemented critical processes, including the Sarbanes-Oxley compliance program post-IPO.

I expanded the Internal Audit Department to a team of 12 and managed a $4M budget. receivedRecommendations.givenAt: May 6, 2011, Allen reported directly to Corey
receivedRecommendations.description:

Corey proved to me his ability to pragmatically challenge the status quo through his perseverance toward leveraging "compliance" activities into value-added activities for the business. headline: AI Transformation Lead @ Fieldguide | Project & Change Management Enthusiast | Bringing order to the disorder until there is no more
about:
With over 15 years of dedicated experience in program management, I am a Human-Centered Integration Specialist who bridges the technical and emotional aspects of organizational transformations. I specialize in driving successful merger and acquisition initiatives, particularly in post-acquisition system integrations for accounting software and ERP implementations.

My approach combines structured project management methodologies with proven change management frameworks to navigate the critical intersection where technical requirements meet human realities—the space where most integration initiatives succeed or fail.

My unique value lies in:
• Building crucial stakeholder relationships during assessment and planning phases
• Identifying and addressing resistance using emotional change management techniques
• Creating effective communication channels between technical teams and end users
• Ensuring higher adoption rates and minimizing productivity disruption

My domain expertise spans cloud computing, machine learning, and finance, complemented by my proficiency in delivery excellence and process improvement. I thrive in dynamic environments, gathering the right stakeholders and maintaining those relationships through implementation to deliver impactful results.

I'm passionate about transforming complex technical challenges into human-centered success stories. Let's connect and explore opportunities to collaborate on transformative projects.

As a marketing executive, I bring extensive experience in driving revenue and elevating companies to industry-leading positions. My approach is data and customer driven, allowing for tailored and relevant experiences that meet buyers where they are, seamlessly across multiple channels, while ensuring a consistent message and brand experience. I take pride in developing high-performing teams that are as passionate about growth as I am. Together, we create a strong marketing presence that secures a leading position in the market.

Central to my philosophy is fostering a seamless integration between sales and marketing, developing a 'one team' mentality focused on unified revenue growth. By partnering closely with all aspects of sales, I have been instrumental in aligning goals and strategies, ensuring that both teams are not only in sync but are also jointly accountable for each step of the revenue cycle. This collaboration has been crucial in driving scalable, repeatable, and efficient revenue growth throughout my career.

I thrive in environments that challenge the status quo and seek a visionary approach to market leadership. Let’s connect to explore how we can drive growth together and turn market opportunities into lasting achievements.

headline: Head of Product @ Fieldguide | AI for Audit & Advisory
about:
I serve startup and growth-stage teams as a product and data science leader.

I've spent the last 15+ years in VC-backed startups, predominantly focused on Vertical SaaS and AI
products.  I bring a confident, thoughtful presence to the leadership team, while embracing the roll-up-your-sleeves, bias-for-action nature of early-stage startups.  My background includes deep focus on B2B SaaS, AI, data science, and building stage-appropriate product and data orgs from scratch.  Success and failure give me a humble-confidence and deep resolve to see more startups thrive.

I also enjoy writing about startup product leadership.  Product Management is different in startups.  The really-tricky, sanity-testing, existential-challenges you face as a startup product leader aren't covered in most product books and blogs.  And sadly, these unspoken differences are often what determine the success and failure of startup product leaders.

I live in Austin with my amazing wife, four kids, and a pet hedgehog 🦔.

Views expressed are my own. 

Image credit: Carlos Alfonso

▪️ Architected a Business Intelligence and Vendor Rebate Management System responsible for 22% of EBITDA, automated analytics workflows that saved 240+ hours annually, and launched Tableau dashboards impacting 40+ executives to drive strategic decisions.

I spearheaded the development of an analytical framework to underpin the strategic management of six product categories, contributing to an impressive $2 billion in annual revenue. Within the Category Management department, I led a team of five direct reports, facilitating their efforts by conceptualizing and constructing sophisticated analytical tools, reporting dashboards, and performance scorecards. These instruments enabled meticulous tracking of strategy execution and outcomes while ensuring compliance with regulatory standards such as the Sabine-Oxley (SOX) Act through diligent management of monthly accruals and forecasts.

Furthermore, I led the pioneering development of a robust Vendor Rebate and Contract Management System, instrumental in driving 22% of EBITDA. Leveraging advanced technologies, I architected a comprehensive Business Intelligence platform and web application tailored to streamline vendor contract lifecycle management, encompassing terms negotiation, rebate tracking, and collections.

Under my guidance, the team conducted rigorous ROI analyses of over 150 vendor agreements, resulting in a notable $3 million enhancement in contractual terms, thus optimizing profitability.

In addition, my introduction of the Procure-to-Pay (P2P) project revolutionized early-pay discount collection processes. By applying Six-Sigma methodology, we achieved an 18% increase in discounts collected within a 12-month period, translating to a significant boost of over $300,000 in EBITDA.

Notably, my contributions were recognized with the Leadership Excellence Award in 2015, underscoring my commitment to surpassing project goals and driving impactful change within the organization.

I led a comprehensive financial reporting and analytics initiative aimed at providing actionable insights to both senior executives and line management. Within this capacity, I supervised a team of three highly skilled Senior Financial Analysts proficient in Tableau, SQL ETL, and adept at extracting and analyzing data from multiple enterprise resource planning (ERP) systems and other relevant sources.

The collective efforts of the analytics team resulted in an impressive annual margin growth exceeding $6.5 million, demonstrating our ability to derive value from data-driven decision-making processes.

Furthermore, I oversaw the development of the Tableau Server Executive Reporting Portal, a sophisticated platform boasting over 100 interactive dashboards catering to the needs of 40 key users across the organization.

In a strategic move to enhance productivity and fortify data governance practices, I implemented a new Tableau Server infrastructure, resulting in significant efficiency gains equivalent to saving 240 staff hours and $20,000 annually.

My contributions were recognized with the prestigious Amp Award in 2014, a distinction conferred upon a select group of individuals out of thousands of employees. This peer-nominated and leadership-voted award underscores my commitment to excellence and innovation in the realm of financial analytics and reporting.

Contributed to the profitability and growth of two of Category Management’s large utility product categories. Informed executive decision making with analysis and modeling of numerous variables and scenarios that included pricing, costs and sourcing, inventory levels, rebates, and discount schemes, and sales gaps. 

Analysis contributed to over $800K in margin improvements.

Formulated complex Tableau model to uncover $3M opportunity for margin lift.

Devised pilot program that netted $100K margin gain from two sales branches uses of profit improvement model.

Inaugurated star schema data warehouse, aligned to profitability improvements.

As lead project manager, coordinated formulation and analysis for O&M activity-based budget. Designed process mapping, devised project schedules, and reported on statuses. Managed data enrichment project to use SAP Business Objects custom queries and data mining.

Authored algorithm that categorized work orders into a defined set of activities.

Project managed $100M Activity-Based Operation and Maintenance Budget.

Composed schedule of YOY cost variation drivers for rate case testimony, as well as operational decision making.

Collaborated on implementation of Supplier Relationship Management (SRM) program, training user teams and advising them on customized scorecards and performance metrics for better alignment of the supply chain. Identified key initiatives for each team to better the supply chain with resultant cost reductions. Tracked program savings; conceptualized training documentation. The catalyst for multiple initiatives to improve inventory stocking, delivery, and logistics cost performance, and RMA resolution.

Guided 14 internal and supplier stakeholder teams through the program; realized over $1.5M sourcing savings yearly.

Analyzed variances and assumptions for monthly budget forecasts for the O&M department and four operating companies. Examined work order transactions, reported on budget and forecast drivers, and conducted cost analyses.

Work order audit recovered $100K; crafted repeatable reporting process that identified unbilled and uncollected revenue.

Retooled Capital Asset Purchasing process with improved supply chain to process capital and track capital expenditures.

Worked closely with each manager and director on budget increase requests by performing cost analysis on budget driving activities, developing the business cases for additional funding.

Lead the job cost controls of 10 major utility and telecommunications engineering contracts.

Responsibilities consisted of; Analysis and reporting of project financials; under billing, gross margin, working capital index, equipment utilization & earned value. Supervision of administrative staff for payroll, revenue, equipment, and payable transaction processing to ensure billing accuracy. Facilitation of the operations annual budgeting & monthly forecasting process, including preparing variance analysis and presenting results to the Finance Director. 

Analysis and reporting of weekly contract profitability and performance of Job cost forecasting for large projects. Development of billing unit schedules through cost and price analysis for all services under contract.

Recovered $200K+ in excessively aged accounts receivable, through an A/R audit and root cause analysis, developed a repeatable process to maintain timely collections.

Managed Project financial controls for 10 utility, construction, and engineering contracts (8M+ annual revenue).

Owned all financial and accounting related functions. Performed financial analysis, reporting, and accounting, including A/P, A/R, job cost accounting, budgeting, cash flow reporting and analysis, job scheduling/cash flow analysis, construction loan payment processing, GL reconciliation, change order processing, payroll processing, payroll taxes, 1099 processing, W-2 processing, financial planning, and projections. 

In addition, I worked with lenders to retrieve construction financing on spec home projects. I also lead the contract processing and development, including Contract writing, subcontract management, bidding, and insurance/license data collection, business license and tax filing; corporate liability insurances, bonding management, and client contract negotiations.

Contributed to the successful completion of two custom home construction contracts valued at $2M+, 1 Spec Home construction project valued at $1M+, and two property subdivisions, a total of 6 custom home lots.

headline: Lead Product Manager @ Fieldguide
about:
I love solving complex problems by building intuitive, user-friendly solutions. With a background in product management, user-centered design, and data analytics, I enjoy turning ideas into real, impactful products that make a difference for users.

At Docusign, I’ve led product development for platform products, from concept to launch, including agreement workflows and third-party integrations. My work has helped expand Docusign's reach into other ecosystems through partner integrations and laid part of the foundation for Intelligent Agreement Management, a new category for agreements. In both products I focused on creating intuitive configuration experiences, reducing complexity, and making it easier for users to set up while cutting down time to publish.

Earlier in my career, I gained hands-on experience in data analytics, data mining, and process automation, helping organizations streamline operations, boost reporting efficiency, and drive smarter decision-making. That data-driven mindset continues to shape how I build and scale products today, especially as I explore the transformative potential of AI-driven automation.

experience.description:
Led the development of a no-code agreement workflow platform, enabling customers to design and implement their agreement processes seamlessly. 

• Launched the first version of Docusign Maestro enabling customers to build end-to-end agreement workflows by integrating DocuSign products with third-party solutions like CRMs.
• Developed and executed the strategy for introducing seven key capabilities as workflow modules, enabling users to integrate them seamlessly into their processes.
• Implemented five core workflow features to aid with usability and simplify workflow creation and management.
• Collaborated closely with engineering and design teams to ensure successful execution, iterating on the platform based on user feedback and research.

Led the design and development of an integrations platform to streamline and expedite the process of connecting third-party systems with Docusign products for both internal teams and external partners.

• Launched four strategic integrations and co-developed the first partner-led integration to showcase extensibility of the platform.
• Delivered a UI platform component that reduced user configuration times by 60%.
• Collaborated with 10 cross-functional teams to define processes and assets for pre-sales activities, provisioning plan, customer onboarding, and support channels to ensure successful and smooth customer enablement.

• Delivered a proof of concept for integrating Docusign's document generation feature within Microsoft Dynamics CRM, validating its value and feasibility.
• Created key deliverables including user scenarios, competitive matrix, product requirements document, and executive summaries with recommendations.
• Defined and prioritized user stories and managed project delivery following the Scrum framework.

experience.position: Business Analyst - Client: The Walt Disney Company
experience.description:
As a Business Analyst for Disney's Financial Systems department, I gathered and analyzed requirements from 18 business teams, assessing information needs, system dependencies, and risks.

• Managed the definition and mapping of over 2,000 data attributes to minimize impacts on downstream systems and users.
• Provided stakeholders with comprehensive project documentation, including business requirement documents, reporting templates, and data flow diagrams.
• Facilitated communication between business and development teams to ensure successful delivery.

As a Strategic Data Analyst, I enhanced operational efficiency by compiling and analyzing weekly Key Performance Indicators, implementing customized database solutions, and creating time-saving tools.

• Developed and implemented database solutions using SQL to standardize data processes.
• Created an invoice compilation tool that saved over 10 hours of manual labor per week.
• Automated and condensed existing reports, reducing report generation by 95% while improving accuracy.

In my role as a Project Analyst for Disney's Creative Costuming department, I optimized labor distribution and production rates by 90% through comprehensive time studies and targeted recommendations. I improved workflows and decision-making by analyzing and mapping garment production processes, and designed space layouts that enhanced storage utilization and reduced cycle times.

publications.title: 3 Ways to Make Your Clients Stick Around
publications.description:
You may think your best customers are the ones who never talk to you and auto-renew every year. But in reality, you’re likely to lose those customers the second they find a better deal elsewhere.

Your best customers are the ones you interact with regularly—the ones who understand exactly what you’re doing for them. Those are the customers who will not only stick around for life, but also refer their friends and family.

Last month, we discussed why a high customer churn rate is bad for business and shared three tips for improving the customer experience.

headline: Software Engineer @ Fieldguide | Data Science & CS @ NUS
about:
Hi everyone, I'm a final-year student at the National University of Singapore, where I am studying Data Science and Computer Science.

In my first two years of university, I juggled academics with internships and freelance roles across various domains, from data science and business analytics to data analytics and software engineering. I intentionally took an unconventional path to explore different career directions and gain hands-on experience. Looking back, I’m grateful for the exposure as it helped me discover the domain of work that I'm interested in and the environments in which I thrive.

Additionally, I was fortunate to have the opportunity to gain global exposure through the NUS Overseas Colleges program by spending time working at startups based in Silicon Valley (2024-2025) and Ho Chi Minh City (2023), where I immersed myself in the tech ecosystems and entrepreneurial culture.

Since 2019, I have been diving into hackathons to solve meaningful problems during my free time. I enjoy rapid ideation, prototyping, and collaborating with teammates to pitch ideas that resonate with relevant stakeholders.

Above all, I love learning, building, and shipping things that make an impact 🚀

receivedRecommendations.description:
Aditya was our Sales Operations Intern at SpotHero in the summer of 2017.  Aditya was a tremendous asset to our team and accomplished a great deal in his time working with us.  Aditya's performance  aligned beautifully with many of SpotHero's most critical values.  "Act like you're in the driver's seat": Aditya was self motivated and worked with a great deal of autonomy.  He was presented with goals and given the freedom to determine how to execute.  He was incredibly thoughtful, hustled, and was ultimately very successful.  "Don't get stuck in traffic": Aditya was tenacious and dogged in his pursuit of goals.  He ran into some pretty significant obstacles and refused to back away from the challenge.  He repeatedly figured out ways over, under, around, and through problems.   "Fuel relationships": Aditya developed outstanding relationships with his co-workers and fellow interns.  "Remember to signal": Aditya is an outstanding communicator.  As his manager, he was in regular communication with me around his accomplishments, progress towards goals, and any blockers.   "Drive growth": Aditya's efforts and results have helped our sales professionals to better understand their assigned markets.  The impact of his work will provide lasting value to our team. 
 Moreover, Aditya drove his own growth, tackling many challenges in areas he initially lacked familiarity with.  He learned and assimilated new skills fearlessly.  Though Aditya was an intern, he was also an incredibly high functioning, fully contributing member of our team.  I'm excited to see where Aditya heads from here.

projects.title: “The Effect of Collaboration in Relationships on Post-Event Memory Recall”
projects.description: This experiment examined the effects of collaboration in relationships (friends vs. strangers) on individual eyewitness memory of a staged robbery.  The hypothesis was that the friend relationship would show more influence on someone’s memory as opposed to the stranger relationship.  This influence would be indicated by friends exhibiting more modifications in memory than the strangers’.  Individuals watched one of two videos of a staged robbery attempt.  Afterward, the participants answered a series of questionnaires to determine their memories of the event. Each video had subtle differences from the other (i.e., in one video the suspect was wearing a red and orange hat and in the other video the suspect was not wearing a hat at all).  Differences between the first and last questionnaires showed whether or not the individual’s memory of the event had altered as a result of collaborating with another person.  The current collected data show no significance t (12) = -.481, p > .05.

receivedRecommendations.givenAt: March 30, 2021, Alice managed Tory directly
receivedRecommendations.description:
Tory is a thoughtful, diligent and highly conceptual designer. She puts a lot of care into providing design solutions that are well-researched, deeply considered and that push the boundaries beyond the expected. 

During the year that Tory contracted for the Slack brand design team, she became a highly valued partner and we came to rely on her as part of the team. She understands the importance of brand consistency and her work was vital to helping us continue to build out the Slack brand. Tory asks great questions in order to get a strategic understanding of project goals and the way she presents her work ensures her stakeholders have a clear understanding of how and why she arrived at her solutions.

Tory is extremely collaborative, open to both giving and receiving feedback, and I always knew that the end results would be stellar. Her thoroughness and thoughtfulness also set a great example for other members of the team. I would jump at the chance to work with Tory again.

receivedRecommendations.givenAt: December 3, 2019, Ewen was Tory’s client
receivedRecommendations.description:
I recently had the opportunity to work with Tory on a full branding package for my new business. I cannot recommend Tory more highly - both in terms of her communication and expertise in guiding me throughout the process - and even more so as a designer. Through every step of the process Tory held the ideal balance of guiding me and seeking my input to create a brand and package that is exactly what I was after.

She started the process by getting to know my business and its 'personality.' She asked very clear questions about what I was after and then took my answers to design our new logo. She came back with several options (something she did throughout the process), and for each option she gave her own insights - but also made it very clear that I should listen to my own gut instincts to guide the process. I was bowled over by what she came up with - the logo I chose is EXACTLY the type of thing I was after, and surpassed my expectations. It's professional, fun, creative, layered, and fits in all of the attributes I asked for.

She then used that logo to guide the rest of our process: setting up colors, fonts, letterhead, social media, business cards, etc. In all cases her ideas were so creative and on-brand, that I actually came to understand branding and its importance in a whole new light just through this process.

Another important note: at a few points along the way I second guessed my answers or changed my mind. Tory took those things - that I know from experience can be frustrating from a client - completely in stride. She was a complete professional who adapted to my requests effortlessly, and weighed in when I was stuck. Any time I was nervous to committing to such big choices for my company, she made it easy to make sure we were moving ahead with the right plan. She never made me feel pressured or rushed, in fact I admired how much of an investment she had in making sure everything felt right before we moved on to the next step.

The cherry on top came in the handoff process, where Tory gave me an extremely comprehensive and highly organized breakdown of my brand assets. Everything is already exactly how I need it to reference it for all applications, and I have a customized guide to refer myself, my teams, or contractors to on how to implement the branding.

Her design skills and creative instincts are unquestionable, and the fact that she knows how to be so organized and professional in implementing the process makes working with her again and recommending her a no brainer.

As a new business, Tory created us a logo and brand that I feel we owe it to ourselves to grow into - that's how rad it is.

headline: Customer Success | Technical Support | Customer Advocacy
about:
At the heart of my professional journey lies a steadfast dedication to customer success, demonstrated through exceptional client communication and problem-solving skills honed at Fi and Peloton Interactive. Navigating complex technical landscapes, I have consistently surpassed customer satisfaction benchmarks and KPIs, reflecting a collective commitment to excellence.

With a focus on collaboration, I've partnered with cross-functional teams to enhance user experiences and streamline the integration of innovative technologies like the Fi Nano microchip program. Championing customer advocacy, my bilingual proficiency has been instrumental in providing empathetic support and fostering meaningful connections with diverse clientele.
topSkills: Problem Solving • Zendesk Customer Service Software • De-escalation • Software Support • Hardware Support

experience.description:
My role blends customer advocacy with hands-on support:

Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues across email, phone, and chat with precision and care.

Guide users through Fieldguide’s features, sharing best practices to help them fully leverage the platform.

Act as the voice of the customer internally; sharing feedback with Engineering, Product, and Design teams to help shape our roadmap.

Support onboarding by assisting with database setup and template creation, ensuring a smooth start and long-term satisfaction.

Keep our help center sharp by contributing to support documentation, FAQs, and self-service tools.

Assist clients with their payroll tax and filing needs, ensuring compliance, accuracy, and exceptional customer service. Navigate complex tax-related inquiries with clarity and professionalism while  maintaining a high standard of client satisfaction.

Key Responsibilities:

Customer Assistance: Respond to client inquiries via email, and chat regarding payroll tax filings, deadlines, and compliance requirements.

Problem Resolution: Troubleshoot and resolve tax-related issues, such as discrepancies, filing errors, or payment concerns, while maintaining a client-focused approach.

Education and Guidance: Provide clear explanations of payroll tax processes, including federal, state, and local regulations, to clients of varying levels of expertise.

Documentation: Accurately document client interactions and resolutions in the company’s CRM system to ensure seamless follow-ups and compliance tracking.

Collaboration: Work closely with internal teams, including Tax Operations, to escalate and resolve complex cases efficiently.

Compliance Monitoring: Stay updated on payroll tax regulations and company policies to provide accurate and up-to-date information to clients.

Process Improvement: Identify recurring issues and suggest process improvements to enhance the client experience and operational efficiency.

Troubleshoot complex technical issues and manage customer expectations while prioritizing more urgent and/or escalated cases, handling on average 30-40 complex technical tickets a day.

Offered compassionate assistance to customers using the 'lost dog mode' feature, aiding in the successful recovery of missing pets.

Delivered extensive account management and technical support for business partners integrating the Fi Nano microchip program.

Flag and debug software and firmware issues and coordinate with Engineering/Product to resolve UX/UI issues, as well as beta test hardware.

Maintain a consistency high CSAT and QA score, and exceed KPIs while addressing customers in a timely manner via email, chat and phone.

Advocate for the customer to coordinate troubleshooting efforts across Engineering, Product, Finance and Support teams to drive customer success.

Field incoming phone calls, live chats, and emails from members and identify the type of assistance needed through appropriate probing questions. 

Troubleshoot issues ranging from hardware warranty replacements to software and streaming video error codes and last mile shipping inquiry's. 

Assisting new hires with service inquiries related to the hardware and software of Peloton equipment; including technical accessories, integration Issues, and ordering replacement parts in a timely manner.

Earned Top Performer in QA (Quality Analysis) for December 2021 and consistently exceeded individual KPI goals through delivering quality work at a fast pace to keep up with user demands.

Ran the store during the holiday season with one other full-time employee. In that time, I learned the importance of rolling up my sleeves and getting to work! I multi-tasked juggling multiple clients, resolved escalations, and maintained one of the best sales KPI's in the region. 

As a result, we finished December 2nd in the region in volume. I also became one of the top 3 best salesman in the company.

I learned that the grass isn't always greener on the other side and returned to Bonobos after a short stint with Suit Supply. 

The second time around I felt confident in my sales skills, advanced suiting product, and tailoring knowledge, but more importantly, resolving complex problems with escalated customers.

 I supported my GM in submitting business recaps, brainstorm activations/events, recruit and interview candidates. 

Our shop became the first store at Scottsdale Quarter to host an event in the summer of 2020 (post Covid-19 shutdown). My "Fall back to work" event was a hit! Our clients received a free headshot with any suit fitting.

Since Walmart is Bonobo's parent company, when Bonobos pulled the plug from working from home we were offered jobs at local Walmarts, Sams Clubs and/or distribution centers. I took the position at my local Walmart and seamlessly fit into the Online Grocery Department which ended up being a gritty, heavy labored experience that helped me lose weight! 

My utmost respect goes out to my longer tenured teammates that did a great job training me and making me feel welcomed for those 4 weeks.

First and only experience thus far with a European company. This job was great because they take their employee training VERY seriously. I spent a week in Dallas learning about suiting fabrics, leather goods and how to pin fabric to pass off to a tailor to complete alterations. 

One aspect of the job I did enjoy was the custom suiting program. The precise measuring, wide availability of fabrics and patterns, and a quick 2-3 week turnaround was a bright selling point with my customers. Achieved top salesman in our Scottsdale location in December 2019 but had a desire to leave after the holiday season since my work/life balance was off and taking a toll on me.

Had a blast introducing e-commerce and converting traditional mall shoppers into Bonobos fans. Contributed to achieving our team's goal by becoming the only Guideshop in the country to hit our monthly sales targets for a full calendar year. Helped clients ranging from college graduates who need a new wardrobe for their first job to professional baseball players in town for spring training.

Scaled a "last call" sample sale event from a Guideshop level to a company wide event during 4th of July weekend to help drive traffic into our slower season.

Helped University of Texas college students fit into our dress shirts, blazers and got them into our LinkedIN photo booth to help give their profile photo a little bit of an extra edge. Soaked up the campus environment and ate some really tasty BBQ throughout the week!

Took a promotion at a new location where visual merchandising was my primary role on the sales floor. One of my favorite experiences is when the Super Bowl Champions New England Patriots stayed at the resort next to us and came in one night for a private shopping session. Didn't meet Tom Brady but still had a blast assisting his teammates!

First job when I moved to Arizona. Met incredible people who inspired me to start running and eventually start a Run Club at our store. I was in the best shape of my life which helped me speak to our products that much better! I helped train the Run Club to run in the 2016 Pats Run, a 4.2 mile run in Tempe in honor of Pat Tillman.

experience.description: Accounts Receivable, Accounts Payable, Expense Management, Bookkeeping, Sales Commission

I handled corporate spending, domestic & international payments, sales commission, invoices, collections, and payment reconciliation as the second accounting and finance hire at the company. I administered fintech integrations, troubleshooting, syncs, implementations, issues and updates including the following:
- Upleveled Forethought’s billing and revenue systems to be ASC 606 compliant by implementing SaaSoptics and producing accurate transaction, invoice, and revenue data by product for current, historical and future deals
- Implemented a sales tax solution by analyzing physical and economic nexus data to assess tax exposure, registering with the states to remit taxes, and reviewing for accuracy each month
- Reconciled ARR between Salesforce and SaaSoptics each month to provide leadership with accurate updates to account for new deals, upgrades, downgrades, and churn
- Managed the Netsuite implementation from a systems perspective to feed current and historical AR and AP data from SaaSoptics, Anrok, Bill.com and Divvy to Netsuite
- Calculated sales commission and programmed commission plan into a software tool for sales visibility into new hire draws, tiered commissions, multi-year SPIFFs, and clawbacks
- Maintained SaaS management and procurement tools for tracking software spend, renewal dates, contracts, user licenses, and utilization to simplify procurement to save the company money on underutilized licenses and provide data for negotiating favorable vendor contracts

I partnered with key stakeholders of Qualtrics and its new parent company, SAP, and lead process adaptations, client success, and financial strategy of subscription renewals. Since we operated on separate CRM and ERP systems, I mediated the process between both companies to share and correct data for forecasting and sales commission. I wrote SQL queries for sales reports and visualized the data in Tableau dashboards for company-wide visibility. I also developed an automated survey system for global offices to escalate and resolve sales-crediting issues among themselves without having to involve leadership.

I managed bulk invoices and collections in Netsuite. I worked with Sales and Customer Success to structure multi-year deals, credits, extensions, upgrades, and downgrades. I performed deal desk/quote-to-cash tasks in Salesforce and troubleshooted CPQ quotes on the front end of thousands of transactions. I created training materials and taught many team members this role.

I spent a summer working alongside experienced portfolio managers to hedge the credit risk of Freddie Mac’s $1.7 Trillion single family guarantee portfolio. I was involved in structuring capital markets and (re)insurance related transactions; supporting the transaction execution process for CRT offerings, which includes developing investor presentations, assessing portfolio risks and cash flows, and performing capital and pricing analyses; and performing ad-hoc and programmatic portfolio management analysis and reporting to support CRT strategy. I also got to develop special projects as assigned by management including research and development on new CRT products, economic analysis, developing presentations for management, project management, and governance support.

about:
coachingbyderek.com

I’m a customer implementation consultant with a background in audit, compliance, and client success — helping organizations streamline processes, adopt new technology, and deliver measurable outcomes. Over the years, I’ve built a reputation for driving impact through strong communication, project management, and a client-first approach.

Outside of my full-time role, I launched Momentum Career Coaching, where I help early-to-mid career professionals land their next role, pivot industries, and earn promotions. Through resume reviews, LinkedIn optimizations, mock interviews, and personalized career strategy, I’ve turned years of informally mentoring colleagues and friends into a structured, results-driven coaching practice.

Whether in SaaS implementation or career coaching, my focus is the same: making complex challenges feel simple, actionable, and achievable.

Matt is a talented front-end architect, who also happened to put his hands on back-end coding and CI/CD tools. He joined Real Magnet early 2016, and we worked together on multiple projects. Driven by natural curiosity and having aspirations for learning and applying new technologies, he led our team transforming front-end infrastructure of a large enterprise application to a new level - from jQuery and AMD modules to webpack, TypeScript, ES6, React, and all neat tools and CLIs.

Matt loves challenges exploring new tech, always on the lookout for best practices, and encourages the team to follow them. We used to have this saying at Higher Logic: “Ask Matt, he knows everything!”.  It was always fun to tackle new problems together, brainstorm crazy solutions, and pair program with so smart team mate! I’ll definitely miss our team work, and hope one day we’ll again work together on something great!

publications.title: RAGNET: End-to-end Training for Neural Graph Retrieval
An Investigation of Overmodification in Pragmatic Agents (Honors Thesis)
publications.description: Speakers' tendency to include redundant information in their referential expressions appears to challenge theories of efficient and pragmatic language use. Specifically, this overmodification occurs more frequently with color modifiers than with size modifiers. While existing hypotheses seek to explain this phenomenon based on various properties of visual scenes or of human language, manipulating these properties in experiments with human participants is often infeasible or impossible. We propose to address this limitation by adopting neural networks as our learning agents. Through a series of controlled experiments, we manipulate properties of the learning environment during language acquisition to study the effect on the agents' downstream language production. We find that overmodification can emerge in pragmatic agents, but that this emergence is sensitive to various design choices regarding model architecture and hyperparameters. We discuss the effect of each of these design choices on overmodification and analyze their benefits and drawbacks, ending with a set of recommendations for future work.

headline: Software Engineering Intern @ Fieldguide | Caltech Class of '26
about:
13. That's how many schools I've attended before college. 13 schools, 13 transitions, and 13 life-changing moments. Making new friends every year was disheartening then, but I wouldn't be where I am today socially if it weren't for those experiences. I learned how to push myself out of my comfort zone and help others feel comfortable and appreciated. These experiences were life-changing because they molded my life doctrine. 

If what you do helps people, why not keep doing it? All my career goals and life decisions revolve around how I can create the greatest good for the greatest number. This approach worked fine till the fateful day I attended an SAT Prep Conference. I stayed back and asked what score I should shoot for. "A score of 1200 is about average, but since you're Asian, you should probably shoot for 1400." It was only when the Harvard lawsuit came out that I learned the importance of valuing diverse perspectives. 

Creating a diverse environment is just as important as developing new ideas and technologies for this simple reason. If the people designing solutions to the world’s problems aren’t representative of the people they are trying to help, then they won’t be able to help those people effectively. That's why I want to pursue research in neural networks. The interdisciplinary nature of neural networks opens up the ways I can help the world, and it also allows me to ensure that a technology that's becoming increasingly pervasive in our world is developed in an ethical and equitable fashion. Change starts today, right here, right now.

That's the essence of who I am and what drives me to strive for new heights, always learning, and always growing. Here are a few fun facts about me!

1) I love playing Dungeons and Dragons, and I've been playing D&D 5e for about 7 years now

2) I've been playing the trumpet for 10 years, and I enjoy playing jazz music and improvising solos

3) I absolutely adore the horror genre, especially films. My favorite is Nosferatu (the first horror movie that was also silent!)

4) I am a play geek. From local playwrights to international superstars, I love poring over and analyzing one of the toughest mediums to portray the human condition through

5) I got stabbed with a javelin in my foot at track practice once. Thankfully nothing serious, but it sure gave me a story to tell

6) I have what some may consider an unhealthy obsession with rap music and African American culture from the perspective of music

projects.title: Sherrif's Office Bike Project
projects.description:
The sheriff's office of my local community commissioned a project to modernize an educational aide used to educate pre-school students about road safety. The aide was a "talking" bike that played a tape with built-in delays that the presenting officer. This combined with LED's for eyes created the illusion of the bike being alive.

The scope of this project included modernizing the components (e.g. - transitioning from a cassette tape to an SD card, using a microcontroller to consolidate the electronics, etc.) and making the presentation interactive by adding new features to make it more personal (e.g. - being able to program the name of a student if it was their birthday, pause/play feature, etc.). 

The constraints of this project mainly boiled down to keeping costs low while working with only one point of entry on the UI. The officer can interact with the bike using only a key fob remote. This presented unique challenges that boiled down to packaging powerful functionality with four buttons. 

The development of this project started with just design and not too much code. I went through several ideas to change the UI such as running a web server and having a website run behind the scenes to having a photoresistor that would read hand gestures. At the end, the simplest and most cost effective solution came down to using a 4-button key fob that communicated with an Arduino Uno board using an RF receiver. The Arduino would communicate with a speaker that could be turned on/off and would perpetually power the LEDs with preprogrammed changes to the expressions.

Since my matriculation at Caltech, I have passed this project down to the AI/CS club I founded my senior year of high school to keep the project closer to the community. It allows me to pass it forward to the next group of passionate developers in my community. I am still a part of the project in a consulting/advisory capacity assisting with the software development aspect of the project.

projects.title: Neural Network From Scratch
projects.description:
For as long as I can remember, I have always been fascinated by how we were able to trick a rock into thinking only by putting lightning in it. I’ve spent every waking moment trying to understand what this rock can do to sate my own alarming curiosity. 

The first step to learning more about my rock was to ask questions, and my curious nature eventually led me to answer the biggest question of all. How can I make my rock learn? I was getting bored of giving my rock every single step and I really wanted it to move out and start living independently. This led me to the glorious world of neural networks. I found great resources online explaining how to start working with neural networks right now, but I came across an issue. Every ‘tutorial’ I found only focused on how to use an existing framework. That was not the depth with which I wanted to evolve my rock. I wanted to know more. I wanted to go deeper. I wanted to answer "Why?"

That's when I committed myself to build my very own neural network from scratch. 6 months of arduous self-research and sleepless nights debugging code led to my very own neural network framework built from scratch. It wasn't easy, but it was worth it for the intimate knowledge that I now posses of every part of rudimentary neural networks. From the backpropgation to the classifiers & optimizers to the neuron itself, I knew why everything was designed the way it was. I could now go beyond just classifying images of dogs & cats and go to the next step of analyzing frames from a video game and telling the character what to do.

The reason this project is ongoing because there is so much more to the world of neural networks than the window I glimpsed through. From GAN's to Q Learning to Quantum Machine Learning, there is so much more I intend to understand at the same level I understood the basic neural network model I worked on. There is joy in unlocking these new capabilities of my rock to improve and create new ways of helping the world.
